The handleResponse method takes an HttpResponse from an AR endpoint and creates the appropriate response object from the com.parworks.androidlibary.response package. Example: HttpResponse responseFromGetSiteInfoEndpoint; GetSiteInfoResponse siteInfo = responseHandler.handleResponse(responseFromGetSiteInfoEndpoint, GetSiteInfoResponse.class);

Parameters:
serverResponse - the http response returned from an AR endpoint
typeOfResponse - the type of response object corresponding to the endpoint
Returns:
the deserialized response object
